<document>
  <properties>
    <author email="mhielen@users.sourceforge.net">Markus Thielen</author>
    <title>eclipse plugin usage xml</title>
  </properties>
  <head>
    <title/>
    <meta http-equiv="CACHE-CONTROL" name="CACHE-CONTROL" content="NO-CACHE"/>
    <meta http-equiv="PRAGMA" name="PRAGMA" content="NO-CACHE"/>
    <meta http-equiv="EXPIRES" content="0"/>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section name="Open mapping file">
      <p>
        When opening a Dozer-mapping-file the Dozer-editor appears. If you want to edit the
        raw XML you can switch to the "source" view.
        <br/>
        <img src="../../images/eclipse-sourcetab.gif"/>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section name="Content Assist">
      <p>
        All the class-a/class-b, field, get-method, set-method, etc -nodes or -attributes automaticly
        show content-assist popups when pressing ctrl+space or the configured WTP-XML content assist
        characters. These can be changed in the preferences.
        <br/>
        <img src="../../images/eclipse-xmlassist.gif"/>
        <br/>
        <img src="../../images/eclipse-xmlassist2.gif"/>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section name="Validation">
      <p>
        The Dozer Plugin validates the Mapping to find out if the mapped class do exist and if the mapped
        fields are accessible.
        <br/>
        <img src="../../images/eclipse-validation.gif"/>
      </p>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>